Acceptance Fee.description: A fee charged by the bank for taking the legal obligation of paying a commercial bill on its maturity date. Generally used when taking over a commercial bill.
Acceptance Fee.label: Acceptance Fee

Additional Security Fee.description: Fee is charged for adding one or more additional securities after loan settlement.
Additional Security Fee.label: Additional Security Fee

Administrative Fee.description: Fee charged by the bank if a customer repays their loan in full before the fixed rate period expires, or makes partial prepayments exceeding a set limit per year during the fixed rate period.
Administrative Fee.label: Administrative Fee

Annual Fee.description: Fee is charged for administration and maintenance of credit facilities, usually for revolving credit loans or credit cards.
Annual Fee.label: Annual Fee

Application Fee.description: Fee is charged for processing and assessment of the application for the loan.
Application Fee.label: Application Fee

Brokerage Fee.description: Fee is charged when a broker has assisted borrowers in finding and obtaining approval for a loan. This fee may be charged to the buyer, seller or both.
Brokerage Fee.label: Brokerage Fee

Cancelled Cheque Fee.description: Fee for cancelling cheques prepared for settlement.
Cancelled Cheque Fee.label: Cancelled Cheque Fee

Cash Benefit Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Cash Benefit Insurance. Cash benefit insurance is related to personal loan products (in particular car loans), and covers the owner if their car is written off/destroyed for any costs of replacing the vehicle (above and beyond the payout they would receive from full comprehensive coverage).
Cash Benefit Insurance.label: Cash Benefit Insurance

Construction Progress Inspection Fee.description: Fee is charged each time a property valuer inspects building works during the course of a property being built in order to ensure that building is in accordance with the plans and expectations.
Construction Progress Inspection Fee.label: Construction Progress Inspection Fee

Consumer Credit Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Consumer Credit Insurance (CCI). CCI is an optional insurance policy that protects borrowers against changes in circumstances that negatively affect their ability to pay back the loan such as death, injury or illness and involuntary unemployment. The premium can generally be added to the loan as a lump sum or can be paid monthly.
Consumer Credit Insurance.label: Consumer Credit Insurance

Deferred Establishment Fee.description: Fee charged when a loan is paid off before a set period has elapsed.
Deferred Establishment Fee.label: Deferred Establishment Fee

Documentation Fee.description: Fee is charged for preparation of loan documents. The amount varies based on the complexity of the loan application.
Documentation Fee.label: Documentation Fee

Early Repayment Admin Fee.description: Fee charged when customer repays the loan earlier than the end of the loan term.
Early Repayment Admin Fee.label: Early Repayment Admin Fee

Early Termination Adjustment Fee.description: Fee payable on fixed rate loans where prepayment amount and specials paid this fixed rate year on the loan is greater than specials repay limit.
Early Termination Adjustment Fee.label: Early Termination Adjustment Fee

Establishment Fee.description: Fee is charged for the establishment of the loan facility. For some financial institutions, this is a general term used for fees that one may incur for the bank to set up a loan which may include Application Fee, Settlement Fee, etc. For some financial institutions, this is the same as an Application Fee.
Establishment Fee.label: Establishment Fee

Excess Cheque Fee.description: Fee for each bank cheque in excess of the allowance.
Excess Cheque Fee.label: Excess Cheque Fee

Extended Warranty Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Extended Warranty Insurance. This insurance (also called mechanical breakdown insurance or motor breakdown insurance (MBI)) commences after your new car warranty ends and provides some cover for the repair or replacement of specific parts.
Extended Warranty Insurance.label: Extended Warranty Insurance

Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Guaranteed Asset Protection (GAP) Insurance. GAP insurance (also called motor equity insurance or shortfall insurance) covers the lender for the difference between what a borrower owes on the car loan, and what the car is insured for under comprehensive car insurance, if the car is written off.
Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance.label: Guarantee Asset Protection Insurance

Inspection Fee.description: A fee charged for the inspection of an asset. An inspection usually occurs to confirm the location of the asset, determine the condition of the asset, and confirm the asset documents match with the physical asset.
Inspection Fee.label: Inspection Fee

LMI.description: Premium charged for taking out Lenders Mortgage Insurance. Lenders Mortgage Insurance is charged by home loan lenders, typically required when the amount to be borrowed is more than 80% of the value of the property. It is either a one-off payment at the time of settlement or can be added to the monthly loan repayments.
LMI.label: LMI

Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.description: Fee is charged when a final search of the title is ordered to ensure that the property is clear from any interest or restrictions that may have been recorded prior to settlement.
Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.label: Land Titles Office Final Search Fee
Land Titles Office Final Search Fee.path: feeTypeList.Land Titles Office Final Search Fee

Land Titles Office Search Fee.description: Fee is charged when title search is ordered to ascertain the ownership of a property and determine whether there are existing encumbrances, covenants or easements that may be recorded on the title.
Land Titles Office Search Fee.label: Land Titles Office Search Fee

Legal Fee.description: Fee is charged to cover legal fees incurred by the lender in arranging the loan.
Legal Fee.label: Legal Fee

Line Fee.description: A fee charged by the bank to keep the credit available for the applicants to use, whether it is a commercial loan, term loan or a credit facility.
Line Fee.label: Line Fee

Loan Fee.description: Fee is charged for the on-going cost of administration and servicing for the loan. Usually on a monthly basis.
Loan Fee.label: Loan Fee

Mortgage Registration.description: Fee is charged by the Title Office to register the lender's mortgage on the title for a security.
Mortgage Registration.label: Mortgage Registration

Motor Vehicle Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out motor vehicle insurance. Motor vehicle insurance is a type of insurance that provides financial protection against physical damage or bodily injury resulting from traffic collisions and against liability that could also arise from incidents in a vehicle.
Motor Vehicle Insurance.label: Motor Vehicle Insurance

Other.description: Fee charged is not described by one of the enumerated values in the list.
Other.label: Other

PPSR Fee.description: A fee associated with registering a non-real estate asset on the Personal Property Securities Register (PPSR) when it is used as security on a loan.
PPSR Fee.label: PPSR Fee

Package Fee.description: A fee charged for packaging a number of products together.
Package Fee.label: Package Fee

Rate Lock Fee.description: A fee charged for fixing an interest rate prior to the advancement of funds under the credit facility.
Rate Lock Fee.label: Rate Lock Fee

Re-documentation Fee.description: Fee is charged when documents such as Loan Agreement or Variation Contract are re-issued prior to settlement due to change requested by either customer or introducer.
Re-documentation Fee.label: Re-documentation Fee

Reduced Equity Fee.description: An alternative name for risk fee.
Reduced Equity Fee.label: Reduced Equity Fee

Risk Fee.description: A fee charged to offset the risk of a high LVR, instead of paying LMI.
Risk Fee.label: Risk Fee

Rollover Fee.description: A fee charged when rolling over a commercial bill.
Rollover Fee.label: Rollover Fee

Security Guarantee Fee.description: A fee charged for each security guarantee associated with the credit facility.
Security Guarantee Fee.label: Security Guarantee Fee

Security Release Fee.description: Fee is charged when a lender removes their legal charge from the security held against a mortgage or loan. This is sometimes called Discharge Fee.
Security Release Fee.label: Security Release Fee

Service Plan.description: A fee associated with an ongoing plan to service the asset.
Service Plan.label: Service Plan

Settlement Fee.description: Fee is charged when borrowers finish paying off the balance on a loan, or refinance with another lender. Also known as Termination Fee or Discharge Fee or Early-exit Fee.
Settlement Fee.label: Settlement Fee

Stamp Duty on Mortgage.description: Fee paid to the State Revenue Office for stamping of mortgage or other security documents.
Stamp Duty on Mortgage.label: Stamp Duty on Mortgage

Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge.description: The stamp duty payable for the discharge of a mortgage.
Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge.label: Stamp Duty on Mortgage Discharge

Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.description: Fee paid to the State Revenue Office for stamping of transfer or other assignments of ownership document.
Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.label: Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property
Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property.path: feeTypeList.Stamp Duty on Transfer of Property

Substitute Security Fee.description: Fee is charged when the current property security of a loan is substituted for another property. This usually occurs when the borrower intends to sell the existing property security.
Substitute Security Fee.label: Substitute Security Fee

Switch Fee.description: Fee is charged when all or part of an existing loan balance will be converted to another product, another type of interest rate (change between fixed and variable) or repayment type (change between interest only payments and principal and interest payments).
Switch Fee.label: Switch Fee

Third Party Document Production Fee.description: Fee is charged when producing a Certificate of Title or other security documents.
Third Party Document Production Fee.label: Third Party Document Production Fee

Title Transfer Fee.description: Fee is charged when there is a transfer of ownership; for example property title transfer or vehicle registration transfer.
Title Transfer Fee.label: Title Transfer Fee

Top Up Establishment Fee.description: Fee charged for the establishment of the top-up loan facility. For some financial institutions, this is a general term used for fees that one may incur for the bank to set up a loan which may include Application Fee, Settlement Fee, etc.
Top Up Establishment Fee.label: Top Up Establishment Fee

Tyre and Rim Insurance.description: Premium charged for taking out Tyre and Rim Insurance. This insurance covers the damage to the tyres and rims outside of an accident. This covers tyres, rims, towing costs, car rentals or accommodation costs.
Tyre and Rim Insurance.label: Tyre and Rim Insurance

Unused Facility Fee.description: A fee charged when a customer has unused limit on their facility. Applies to commercial bills only.
Unused Facility Fee.label: Unused Facility Fee

Valuation Fee.description: A fee charged for the assessment of the value of the security.
Valuation Fee.label: Valuation Fee

Withdrawal of Caveat Fee.description: Fee is charged when caveat will be withdrawn/removed and lodged to the corresponding land or property information office.
Withdrawal of Caveat Fee.label: Withdrawal of Caveat Fee

Withdrawal of Writ Fee.description: Fee is charged for the removal of a writ recorded against a title.
Withdrawal of Writ Fee.label: Withdrawal of Writ Fee
